SENATE JOINT RESOLUTION 1043
By McNally
A RESOLUTION to honor Oak Ridge, Tennessee, as the
"Birthplace of the Nuclear Navy," commend the
work of Admiral Hyman G. Rickover and Dr.
Alvin M. Weinberg, and memorialize the
launching of the USS Nautilus.
WHEREAS, Oak Ridge, Tennessee, created during World War II as a centerpiece of the
Manhattan Project, became a nationally significant center of nuclear science and engineering,
and its people and institutions have continued that legacy of innovation and public service; and
WHEREAS, Oak Ridge National Laboratory—known in its earliest years as Clinton
Laboratories—helped spread nuclear knowledge through training and research that influenced
early capability in nuclear reactor technology; and
WHEREAS, Admiral Hyman G. Rickover, widely recognized for his decisive leadership
in establishing naval nuclear propulsion, was associated with early reactor education and
training connected to Oak Ridge, helping to accelerate the expertise required for the United
States Nuclear Navy; and
WHEREAS, we specifically commend the visionary leadership and public service of
Admiral Hyman G. Rickover, whose exacting standards shaped the United States Nuclear Navy,
and Dr. Alvin M. Weinberg, a longtime leader in reactor science and national service whose
work helped advance peaceful nuclear technology and the knowledge base essential to naval
nuclear propulsion; and
WHEREAS, Oak Ridge's K-25 Site and its successor enrichment operations contributed
enriched uranium for the USS Nautilus and for many naval nuclear propulsion reactors that
followed, helping sustain the nation's Nuclear Navy; and
SJR1043
016924
- 1 -

WHEREAS, the USS Nautilus (SSN-571), the world's first nuclear-powered submarine,
was launched on January 21, 1954, marking a historic turning point in naval warfare and
maritime endurance; and
WHEREAS, Oak Ridge's contributions—through scientific research, engineering
innovation, workforce excellence, and national service—form an enduring part of the foundation
upon which the United States Nuclear Navy was built and continues to operate; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE ONE HUNDRED FOURTEENTH
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE HOUSE OF
REPRESENTATIVES CONCURRING, that we honor Oak Ridge, Tennessee, as the "Birthplace
of the Nuclear Navy," commend the work of Admiral Hyman G. Rickover and Dr. Alvin M.
Weinberg, and memorialize the launching of the USS Nautilus (SSN-571) on January 21, 1954.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
